The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Saturday, July 03, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 Tata Football Academy graduate Habibur Rahman Mondal has been asked by the court to sign for Mohun Bagan, club secretary Balaram Chowdhury told reporters on Friday. 				 																																																	The city civil court has asked Habibur to sign for us and we will do it soon, Chowdhury said. Mohun Bagan coach Subrata Bhattacharya, however, insisted the player have to undergo a trial to make it to the squad. Habibur, it may be recalled, had received payment from Mohun Bagan, but later decided to switch to East Bengal. The matter subsequently went to court, which gave its verdict in Mohun Bagans favour, Chowdhury said. 				 																																																	Meanwhile, Subrata expressed satisfaction with the current wards and said he was looking forward to the upcoming season with much optimism. The current team is younger, energetic and running well in comparison to last seasons lot and Im quite hopeful. Ive a number of plans with this team. , Subrata maintained. 				 																																																	FOOTBALL: Exhibition tie  East Bengal vs Mohammedan Sporting at Vidyasagar Stadium, Barasat, from 3 pm l CFL first division group A  City AC vs SAIL (Mohun Bagan); ECLSA vs Customs (Md. Sp.); Aryan Club vs Taltala DS (SAP-II); Muslim Inst. vs Kidderpore (Tarun Sangha); Milan Bithee (Howrah) vs Police AC (R. Sarobar); Kalighat vs BNR (SAP-I); Howrah Union vs WB Police (East Bengal)  all matches from 3.30 pm l CFL 4th amp; 5th divisions  matches at various grounds from 4 pm.				 																																																	ROWING: Merchants Cup regatta finals at Rabindra Sarobar from 4 pm.
